    "The development of copyright laws in eighteenth century began to formalize the notion of intellectual property, reinforcing the link between a work and its creator (Rose 2002).",
    "These factors collectively contributed to a cultural and institutional framework that increasingly celebrated and recognized individual authorship.",
    "It was followed by the rise of copyright and licensing.",
    "With it, the author became a role that is entitled to, not ontologically present.",
    "In other words, role of author is given to the people that produced the content-not to those who are willing to produce but still did not."
